Presidents Reagan and Clinton both struggled with welfare reform,
responding to public pressure.  Both agreed a work provision must be
included.

Reagan's 1987 plan was criticized for too little emphasis on work, and
in 1993 Clinton proposed job training and work for enrollees.

Other countries struggled with mounting welfare costs.</SUM>
